HEADWORD: Fluxionary
<hw>Flux"ion*a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Fluxional.</def> <rj><au>Berkeley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or caused by, an
increased flow of blood to a part; congestive; <as>as, a
<ex>fluxionary</ex> hemorrhage</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fluxionist</ent>⟦br⟧
